******
[2] Denmark
Date: Tue 12 Aug 2014
Source: The Copenhagen Post [edited]
http://cphpost.dk/news/listeria-outbreak-in-denmark-has-now-claimed-12-lives-in-12-months.10469.html


Since September last year [2013], 12 people have died of listeriosis and a further 8 have been infected after consuming some bad 'rullepoelse' sandwich meat.

The food product authorities Foedevarestyrelsen [Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Fisheries] suspect that the bad meat originated from Joern A Rullepoelser in Hedehusene near Copenhagen and have closed down the producer. [The meat producer was ordered shut late Mon 11 Aug 2014, and all products recalled (http://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/10-feared-dead-denmark-listeria-outbreak-24943819)].

The 20 infected patients consist of 11 women and 9 men aged 43-89 from various parts of Denmark, according to the national serum institute, Statens Seruminstitut.

"From September 2013 until today [12 Aug 2014], 20 patients have been registered suffering from listeriosis, which is an aspect of the outbreak," Statens Seruminstitut wrote in a press release.

"Most cases have however occurred recently. In June, July, and August [2014], 15 cases have been registered alone."

[Byline: Christian Wenande]

